# Traditional Chinese Medicine Daily Schedule

| Time | TCM Perspective | Recommended Activities |
|---|---|---|
| 5:00–7:00 | Large Intestine Meridian Active | Wake up, bowel movement, drink warm water |
| 7:00–9:00 | Stomach Meridian Active | Eat breakfast (very important) |
| 9:00–11:00 | Spleen Meridian Active | Study, work, focused thinking, high mental efficiency |
| 11:00–13:00 | Heart Meridian Active | Lunch and short rest |
| 13:00–15:00 | Small Intestine Meridian Active | Digestion and nutrient absorption; suitable for lighter work |
| 15:00–17:00 | Bladder Meridian Active | Exercise and physical activity |
| 17:00–19:00 | Kidney Meridian Active | Eat a light dinner, avoid eating too late |
| 19:00–21:00 | Pericardium Meridian Active | Relaxation, companionship, meditation |
| 21:00–23:00 | Triple Burner (San Jiao) Meridian Active | Prepare for sleep, reduce stimulation |
| 23:00–1:00 | Gallbladder Meridian Active | Deep sleep (very important) |
| 1:00–3:00 | Liver Meridian Active | Liver restoration and emotional regulation |
| 3:00–5:00 | Lung Meridian Active | Maintain quiet and deep sleep |

